Follow these steps:

0. First of all, clone the suite scripts that you will use:
  - git clone https://github.com/monanadmin/scripts_CD-CT.git
Switch to temporary correct branch "mylocal_version_0.2.1"
  - git checkout mylocal_version_0.2.1

1. Install spack:
You can use the install_spack.bash script in scripts_CD-CT/scripts:
  - run install_spack.bash <your_spack_dir>

2. Install the MPAS dependencies and other packs by spack:
Inside spack run:
  - source <your_spack_dir>/env.sh
  - spack compiler find
    # (important check which version of gcc compiler you have available, and use it stead of gcc@11.4.0 bellow!)
  - spack install mpas-model%gcc@11.4.0 ^parallelio+pnetcdf
  - spack load --only dependencies mpas-model%gcc@11.4.0
  - spack load --list
  - spack install wps@4.3.1%gcc@11.4.0
  - spack load --only dependencies mpas-model%gcc@11.4.0 wps@4.3.1%gcc@11.4.0 
  - spack load --list
    # (important check if the ungrib.exe was installed in wps directory.)
  - spack install metis
  - spack load --only dependencies mpas-model%gcc@11.4.0 wps@4.3.1%gcc@11.4.0 metis
  - spack load --list

3. Clone this scripts pack, and use the laptop branch :
  - git clone https://github.com/monanadmin/scripts_CD-CT.git
  - git checkout mylocal_version_0.2.1

4. Download the data pack into scripts_CD-CT/datain directory:
  wget https://ftp.cptec.inpe.br/pesquisa/dmdcc/volatil/Renato/scripts_CD-CT_datain.tgz
  wget https://ftp.cptec.inpe.br/pesquisa/dmdcc/volatil/Renato/gfs.t00z.pgrb2.0p25.f000.2024080800.grib2
  # for other CI dates: (maybe put that in script 2)
  # wget https://ftp.ncep.noaa.gov/data/nccf/com/gfs/prod/gfs.20240819/00/atmos/gfs.t00z.pgrb2.0p25.f000
  # rename it into a gfs-ci name that the script is waiting for: gfs.t00z.pgrb2.0p25.f000.2024081900.grib2

  untar it and copy the direcotries to be like this:
  scripts_CD-CT/datain/fixed
  scripts_CD-CT/datain/WPS_GEOG
  scripts_CD-CT/datain/2024080800/gfs.t00z.pgrb2.0p25.f000.2024080800.grib2

5. Fill the PNETCDF and NETCDF vars with their correspondent path in scripts_CD-CT/scripts/setenv.bash script:
  use "spack find -p netcdf-c parallel-netcdf" to find the correct path and put them into the setenv.bash script
  or automatically: $(spack location -i pacote)
  # Libraries paths:
  export NETCDF=
  export PNETCDF=


6. Install the MONAN MODEL: ok!
  - run scripts_CDCT/scripts/1.install_monan.bash https://github.com/monanadmin/MONAN-Model.git 1.0.0

7. Cerate your meshes and CIs files: ok!
  - run 2.pre_processing.bash

8. Run the model:
  - run 3.run_model.bash

9. Post-processing the MODEL output:
  - run 4.run_post.bash

10. Now you can see the fields using GrADS, NCView, NCL, or similar...
